of streams & rivers - varieties of Earth,
result; fitted for all the different
modifications of [underline]vegetable Life. -[/underline]
In Plains - in vallies & on the low
hills of mountains, they support plenty
& trees subservient to the nourishment
& shelter of the superior animals,
& to the uses of Man. - On heights
where the larger plants are capable
of growing in consequence of the
intensity of the cold, or the force
of the blast, grasses are still
found, & vegetable life extends
its empire by means of mosses
& lichens, to the limits of perpetual
snow. -
-- When the [underline]effects[/underline] for which

