Indeed
[deletion]&[/deletion] there is no city in Europe more happily
situated in this respect than Dublin.
Its position is such that were a geological
academy to be established it could
not be fixed in a more advantageous
spot - The mountains around us
contain all the varieties of the
Primary rocks; the strata beneath our
feet are secondary: - & the sides of
vallies in the neighbourhood afford
abundance of mineral veins -

